mibatmInterfaceProfileTable.name: mibatmInterfaceProfileTable
mibatmInterfaceProfileTable.description: A list of mibatmInterfaceProfile profile entries.

mibatmInterfaceProfileEntry.name: mibatmInterfaceProfileEntry
mibatmInterfaceProfileEntry.description: A mibatmInterfaceProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibatmInterfaceProfile profile.

atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_Phy.name: atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_PhysicalAddress_Shelf
atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_Phy.description: The number of the shelf that the addressed physical device resides on.

atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_Phy.name: atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_PhysicalAddress_Slot
atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_Phy.description: The number of the slot that the addressed physical device resides on.

atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_Phy.name: atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_PhysicalAddress_ItemNumber
atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_Phy.description: A number that specifies an addressable entity within the context of shelf and slot.

atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_Log.name: atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_LogicalItem
atmInterfaceProfile_InterfaceAddress_Log.description: A number that specifies an addressable logical entity within the context of a physical address.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Enabled.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Enabled
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Enabled.description: SVC signalling (Q.93b) is enabled on this link.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddress_NumberingPlan
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.description: Numbering plan for an SVC address

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddress_E164NativeAddress
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.description: An SVC address in a native E.164 format.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddress_AesaAddress_Format
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.description: An AESA address format used to define this SVC address.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddress_AesaAddress_IdpPortion_Afi
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.description: An Authority and Format Identifier(AFI) for AESA address. Must be defined for every AESA address.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddress_AesaAddress_IdpPortion_Idi
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.description: An Initial Domain Identifier (IDI) portion of the AESA address.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddress_AesaAddress_DspPortion_HoDsp
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.description: A High-Order Domain-Specific Part of AESA address. The IDP portion determine the format of the HO-DSP.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddress_AesaAddress_DspPortion_Esi
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.description: An End System Identifier (ESI) which uniquely identifies the end system within the specified subnetwork.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddress_AesaAddress_DspPortion_Sel
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_AtmAddres.description: A selector (SEL) field that may be used by the end system.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_InsertCal.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_InsertCallingPartyAddr
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_InsertCal.description: Insert ATM address of this interface in calling party address IE during call setup.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_MaxRestart
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Maximum number of unacknowledged tx RESTART.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_MaxStatenq
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Maximum number of unacknowledged tx STATUS ENQ.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T301Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for alerting supervision function. This timer is started on receipt of ALERT in Call received/delivered state and stopped when CONNECT is received.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T303Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after SETUP is sent. This timer is stopped when the CONNECT, CALL PROCEEDING, or RELEASE COMPLETE is received.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T306Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for a RELEASE_COMPLETE to be received after a release has been sent.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T308Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after RELEASE is sent. This is a release indication timer. This timer is started when the RELEASE message is sent and normally is stopped when the RELEASE or RELEASE COMPLETE is received.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T309Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for Q.SAAL to reconnect. After this time, calls are dropped. When set to 0, a default value based on an ATM signaling protocol will be used.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T310Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after SETUP is received. Also called the CALL PROCEEDING timer.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T313Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after CONNECT is sent. Also called the connect request timer. It is started when the CONNECT is sent and stopped when the CONNECT ACKNOWLEDGE is recieved.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T316Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after RESTART is sent. Also called the restart request timer. It is started when the RESTART is sent and stopped when the RESTART ACKNOWLEDGE is recieved.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T317Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for internal clearing of call references. This timer is started as a result of a restart and cleared when all the internal call references are cleared. Should be less than the the likely value of T316 of the peer.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T322Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after STATUS ENQ is sent.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T331Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for internal clearing of call references.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T333Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for internal clearing of call references.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T397Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for internal clearing of call references.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T398Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for receipt of a response to a DROP PARTY that was sent.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T399Ms
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer (in msec) for receipt of a response to an ADD PARTY that was sent.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_SaalRetryMs
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Timer value for retrying AAL_ESTABLISH messages.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T303NumReties
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Number of times SETUP could be resent in case of T303 timer expiry.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T308NumRetries
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Number of times RELEASE could be sent in case of T308 timer expiry.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T316NumRetries
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Number of times RESTART could be sent in case RESTART ACK is not received withinn T316 timer expiry.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_T322NumRetries
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: Number of times STAT ENQ could be sent before a response is received within the T322 timer expiry.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptions_AssignVpiVci
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_Q93bOptio.description: In the case of UNI4.0 and PNNI this parameter specifies who assigns the VPI/VCI. TRUE will allow the local stack and FALSE will let the partner stack to assign.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_MaxCc
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: Maximum number of control PDU (BGN, END, RESYNC) retransmissions.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_MaxPd
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: Maximum number of Sequenced data PDU's between poll.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_TccMs
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: Retry time (in msec) for control PDU's(BGN, END, RESYNC).

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_TpollMs
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: Poll sent (in msec) when active. When set to 0, a default value based on an ATM signaling protocol will be used.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_TkeepaliveMs
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: Poll sent (in msec) when in transient state. When set to 0, a default value based on an ATM signaling protocol will be used.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_TnoresponseMs
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: STAT received at least this period(in msec). When set to 0, a default value based on an ATM signaling protocol will be used.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_TidleMs
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: Poll sent (in msec) when idle -- UNI 3.1, only.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_PollAfterRetransmission
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: Specifies after retransmitting PDUs whether a POLL must be sent before sending any further PDUs.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_RepeatUstat
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: Specifies whether two USTAT messages should be sent each time it is required to be sent.

atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.name: atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOptions_UstatRspToPoll
atmInterfaceProfile_SvcOptions_QsaalOpti.description: Specifies whether a USTAT should be sent in response to a POLL indicating an out of sequence PDU.
